WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.100
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.100 --> 00:06.033
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.033 --> 00:10.400
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.400 --> 00:12.734
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.734 --> 00:14.567
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.567 --> 00:16.367
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:16.367 --> 00:18.800
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.800 --> 00:21.567
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:24.133 --> 00:25.300
WE'VE COME TO YOU

00:25.300 --> 00:27.367
BECAUSE WE HAVE
A VERY BIG PROBLEM.

00:27.367 --> 00:29.233
AND WHO BETTER TO COME TO
THAN YOU?

00:29.233 --> 00:31.000
WE HAD NO IDEA
PLANNING A WEDDING

00:31.000 --> 00:32.500
WAS GONNA BE SO DIFFICULT.

00:32.500 --> 00:35.000
IT'S LIKE RIDING A POGO STICK
IN A MINEFIELD --

00:35.000 --> 00:36.967
<i>BOOM! </i>BOING!

00:36.967 --> 00:39.367
<i>BOOM! </i>BOING!

00:39.367 --> 00:44.100
COME ON, WHAT'S TAKING YOU GUYS
SO LONG?!

00:45.300 --> 00:46.667
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON!

00:54.467 --> 00:56.000
[ SIGHS ]

00:56.000 --> 01:01.500
[ Voice breaking ] THOSE ARE
THE MOST <i>BEAUTIFUL </i>DRESSES...

01:01.500 --> 01:03.900
I HAVE EVER SEEN!

01:03.900 --> 01:06.100
OH, NO.

01:06.100 --> 01:09.767
TOPANGA, DO YOU THINK MAYBE
YOU'RE A LITTLE TOO EMOTIONAL

01:09.767 --> 01:12.500
TO MAKE THE RIGHT DECISION
ABOUT THIS?

01:12.500 --> 01:16.667
THOSE ARE THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
DRESSES I HAVE --

01:16.667 --> 01:18.567
OKAY, OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

01:18.567 --> 01:21.300
WHERE'S MORGAN? I WANT TO SEE
HOW MY FUTURE SISTER LOOKS.

01:21.300 --> 01:23.500
HEY, MORGAN, COME ON OUT.

01:23.500 --> 01:25.133
SHARE THE JOY.

01:28.667 --> 01:31.200
WHAT ARE YOU -- PSYCHO?

01:31.200 --> 01:35.133
MORGAN,
YOU LOOK SO BEAUTIFUL.

01:35.133 --> 01:37.300
WE LOOK LIKE CLOWNS!

01:37.300 --> 01:38.900
<i>BEAUTIFUL </i>CLOWNS.

01:38.900 --> 01:41.200
CIRQUE DU SOLEIL CLOWNS.

01:41.200 --> 01:44.667
NO, HORN-HONKIN',
BIG-SHOE-WEARIN' CLOWNS.

01:44.667 --> 01:45.934
HONEY...

01:45.934 --> 01:48.834
SHUT UP!

01:48.834 --> 01:51.600
I AIN'T WEARIN' IT.

01:51.600 --> 01:55.400
OKAY. SO, YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS A LITTLE CONTROVERSY

01:55.400 --> 01:57.734
OVER THE BRIDESMAIDS'
DRESSES...

01:57.734 --> 02:01.200
BUT I THOUGHT THAT IF I JUST
<i>REALLY </i>EXPRESSED MY FEELINGS,

02:01.200 --> 02:03.967
EVERYONE WOULD UNDERSTAND.

02:03.967 --> 02:05.967
SEE?

02:05.967 --> 02:08.567
THEY COME WITH PARASOLS!

02:08.567 --> 02:10.867
AND THE BEST PART

02:10.867 --> 02:12.233
IS THAT AFTER THE WEDDING,

02:12.233 --> 02:14.500
YOU GUYS ARE GONNA WANT
TO WEAR THESE DRESSES

02:14.500 --> 02:18.233
OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

02:18.233 --> 02:20.800
UGH!

02:20.800 --> 02:23.100
DIE, DRESS, DIE!

02:23.100 --> 02:24.467
DIE! DIE!

02:24.467 --> 02:26.367
OH, MY GOD!

02:26.367 --> 02:27.934
OKAY, HONEY!

02:27.934 --> 02:29.934
IT'S DEAD!
IT'S DEAD!

02:29.934 --> 02:32.367
IT CAN'T HURT YOU ANYMORE.

02:32.367 --> 02:34.100
OKAY.

02:34.100 --> 02:35.500
SWEETIE, HOW YOU DOING?

02:35.500 --> 02:37.600
YOU GOOD?
YOU OKAY? OKAY.

02:37.600 --> 02:40.400
WELL, ABOUT THESE LOVELY,
LOVELY DRESSES...

02:40.400 --> 02:42.000
MAYBE IT'S POSSIBLE...

02:42.000 --> 02:43.300
THAT WE ARE NOT...

02:43.300 --> 02:44.667
LOVELY ENOUGH...

02:44.667 --> 02:46.133
FOR THEM.

02:46.133 --> 02:49.233
JUST CUT THE CRAP.
AT LEAST MORGAN WAS HONEST.

02:49.233 --> 02:50.767
WELL, THAT'S IT.

02:50.767 --> 02:53.567
IF YOU GUYS
CAN'T PUT ON THESE DRESSES

02:53.567 --> 02:56.767
AND GET CAUGHT UP IN THE MAGIC
OF MY SOUTHERN-BELLE WEDDING,

02:56.767 --> 02:58.700
[ Crying ]
THEN WHO NEEDS Y'ALL?!

02:58.700 --> 03:02.800
YOU'RE FROM PHILADELPHIA,
STUPID!

03:02.800 --> 03:05.233
Cory:
A SOUTHERN-BELLE WEDDING...

03:07.700 --> 03:10.400
WHEN, UH, WHEN DID WE
DECIDE ON THAT?

03:10.400 --> 03:12.834
EVERY WEDDING HAS TO HAVE
A THEME, CORY.

03:12.834 --> 03:14.767
FOR WHAT REASON,
MY DARLING?

03:14.767 --> 03:16.100
BECAUSE IT DOES.

03:16.100 --> 03:18.667
FOR WHAT REASON,
MY DARLING?

03:18.667 --> 03:22.000
I WANT OURS TO BE
"GONE WITH THE WIND."

03:22.000 --> 03:26.367
WELL, FRANKLY, MY DEAR,
THAT'S NOT THE THEME <i>I </i>WANT.

03:26.367 --> 03:27.900
REALLY? WHAT'S YOURS?

03:27.900 --> 03:30.400
"HAVE A NOSH
WITH CORY AND TOPANGA."

03:30.400 --> 03:32.900
DO YOU SEE
WHAT I'M DEALING WITH HERE?

03:32.900 --> 03:35.033
PLUS, WE HAVE A GUESTLIST
OF 270.

03:35.033 --> 03:37.033
AND A HALL THAT SEATS 80.

03:37.033 --> 03:39.967
WE'RE NOT PANICKING. WE KNOW
A LOT OF PEOPLE WON'T SHOW.

03:39.967 --> 03:42.834
AND MANY OF THE OLD PEOPLE
HAVE SHRUNK.

03:42.834 --> 03:45.300
[ Crying ]
I MISS GRANDPA POPPY.

03:45.300 --> 03:46.934
WE ALL DO, HONEY.

03:46.934 --> 03:49.100
NO ONE SHOULD DIE IN PRISON!

03:49.100 --> 03:50.567
SEE, WHILE EVERYONE ELSE

03:50.567 --> 03:52.834
MAY BE GOING CRAZY
OVER THIS WEDDING,

03:52.834 --> 03:55.600
WE, AT LEAST, HAVE BEEN
KEEPING IT TOGETHER.

03:55.600 --> 03:57.400
FOR OUR HONEYMOON --

03:57.400 --> 04:00.600
HONEYMOO-OON!

04:00.600 --> 04:03.367
WE CAN GO TREKKING IN PERU,
SCUBA DIVING IN THE CARIBBEAN,

04:03.367 --> 04:05.400
OR RIVER RAFTING
DOWN THE COLORADO.

04:05.400 --> 04:07.500
IT'S NOT NECESSARY.

04:07.500 --> 04:09.367
CORY, I'VE MADE
A TON OF SUGGESTIONS,

04:09.367 --> 04:11.200
AND YOU DON'T LIKE
ANY OF THEM.

04:11.200 --> 04:12.800
WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE
YOU HAVEN'T MENTIONED

04:12.800 --> 04:14.834
THE ONE PLACE
THAT <i>I </i>WANT TO GO.

04:14.834 --> 04:18.100
WHERE IS THAT?
YOU KNOW.

04:18.100 --> 04:19.100
CORY!

04:19.100 --> 04:21.033
I WANT IT.

04:21.033 --> 04:23.233
CORY, I'M BEGINNING TO THINK
THAT THIS WEDDING IS JUST

04:23.233 --> 04:24.834
A PRELUDE TO SEX FOR YOU.

04:24.834 --> 04:26.834
THAT'S BRILLIANT, SHERLOCK.

04:26.834 --> 04:28.467
OH, SO YOU'RE
JUST MARRYING ME

04:28.467 --> 04:29.900
SO WE CAN CONSUMMATE
OUR RELATIONSHIP?

04:29.900 --> 04:32.834
ME AND 900 MILLION
OTHER GUYS.

04:32.834 --> 04:35.000
I'M BEGINNING TO THINK
YOU'D BE FINE

04:35.000 --> 04:37.600
IF WE JUST SPENT OUR
HONEYMOON IN ANY OLD HOTEL.

04:37.600 --> 04:39.033
OR IN THE ROAD.

04:40.734 --> 04:42.500
CORY, THAT'S SICK.

04:42.500 --> 04:44.767
THAT'S SICK?
I'M SICK?

04:44.767 --> 04:46.667
YOU KNOW WHAT'S
SICK, EVERYONE?

04:46.667 --> 04:50.033
WE HAVE BEEN IN
A RELATIONSHIP FOR 17 YEARS,

04:50.033 --> 04:52.700
AND DO YOU KNOW WHAT I'VE
GOTTEN IN ALL OF THAT TIME?

04:52.700 --> 04:55.400
LET ME TOUCH SOMETHING!

05:01.467 --> 05:03.300
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT YOU OWE ME?

05:05.467 --> 05:06.600
YES.

05:06.600 --> 05:08.233
DO YOU INTEND
TO PAY ME?

05:09.600 --> 05:11.367
YES.
IN THE ROAD?

05:11.367 --> 05:13.367
YES. IN THE ROAD.

05:13.367 --> 05:16.934
AND YOU'LL CALL ME
DON FRANCISCO?

05:19.767 --> 05:20.934
YES.

05:20.934 --> 05:22.600
YES, WHO?

05:22.600 --> 05:24.600
YES, DON FRANCISCO.

05:25.700 --> 05:27.500
ALL RIGHT, I'LL MARRY YOU.

05:34.567 --> 05:36.467
THAT WAS ONLY
THE BEGINNING.

05:36.467 --> 05:38.400
PLANNING THE WEDDING
GOT A LOT WORSE...

05:38.400 --> 05:40.400
BECAUSE THE NEXT THING
I HAD TO DO

05:40.400 --> 05:41.600
WAS PICK A BEST MAN.

05:41.600 --> 05:44.000
OBVIOUSLY, THE CHOICE
CAME DOWN TO MY BROTHER

05:44.000 --> 05:46.100
OR MY BEST FRIEND.

05:46.100 --> 05:48.667
HEY, COR, LISTEN --
AS FAR AS THE WEDDING GOES,

05:48.667 --> 05:50.600
I'M SURE YOU'RE UNDER
A LOT OF PRESSURE

05:50.600 --> 05:52.667
ABOUT THE WHOLE
BEST-MAN SITUATION.

05:52.667 --> 05:54.400
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THAT.

05:54.400 --> 05:56.667
I THINK
YOU SHOULD PICK ERIC.

05:56.667 --> 05:58.500
IT'S THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

05:58.500 --> 05:59.667
MY BEST FRIEND --

05:59.667 --> 06:02.600
MY <i>ABSOLUTE </i>BEST FRIEND
WHO I LOVE --

06:02.600 --> 06:05.200
CORY, WE GET IT.
GET ON WITH IT.

06:05.200 --> 06:08.500
MY POINT IS,
HE'S THE GREATEST GUY THERE IS.

06:08.500 --> 06:10.500
YOU'RE THE GREATEST GUY
THERE IS.

06:10.500 --> 06:13.934
HEY, IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
I UNDERSTAND COMPLETELY.

06:13.934 --> 06:16.600
HE'S FAMILY. HE'S BLOOD.
HE'S YOUR BROTHER.

06:16.600 --> 06:19.033
NO BOND
IS MORE SACRED THAN THAT.

06:22.900 --> 06:24.934
YOU KNOW
HE'S GONNA DROP THE RINGS

06:24.934 --> 06:26.400
DOWN THE MINISTER'S PANTS.

06:26.400 --> 06:28.467
AND DIVE RIGHT IN
AFTER THEM.

06:28.467 --> 06:31.500
WITH BOTH HANDS,
CAUSING THE MINISTER TO FREAK.

06:31.500 --> 06:32.834
AND COUGH.

06:32.834 --> 06:34.200
AND COUGH.

06:34.200 --> 06:36.100
AND THEN KNOCK OVER
THE CANDLES

06:36.100 --> 06:38.200
AND SET THE ENTIRE CHURCH
ON FIRE.

06:38.200 --> 06:40.000
AND HERE COMES
THE FIRE DEPARTMENT

06:40.000 --> 06:43.000
WITH THEIR HOSES AND AXES,
CHOPPING UP EVERYTHING IN SIGHT,

06:43.000 --> 06:44.600
AND TOPANGA'S GONNA BLAME...

06:44.600 --> 06:46.767
ME.

06:46.767 --> 06:53.367
AND I DON'T GET NOTHIN'
ON THE HONEYMOO-OON!

06:53.367 --> 06:55.133
SHAWN,
GIVE ME ONE GOOD REASON

06:55.133 --> 06:56.900
I SHOULD PICK ERIC
AS THE BEST MAN.

06:56.900 --> 07:02.300
BECAUSE I'M BIGGER
THAN HE IS AND <i>STRONGER  </i>
THAN HE IS.

07:03.967 --> 07:05.500
SO?

07:05.500 --> 07:06.934
SO? SO?!

07:06.934 --> 07:08.900
DON'T YOU WANT SOMEBODY
WHO'S STRONG ENOUGH

07:08.900 --> 07:10.700
TO LIFT YOU UP
FOR THE TRADITIONAL

07:10.700 --> 07:12.567
"FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW" DANCE?

07:12.567 --> 07:15.133
I'VE ACTUALLY NEVER HEARD
OF THE DANCE.

07:15.133 --> 07:16.567
I'LL SHOW YOU.

07:16.567 --> 07:17.834
ERIC, I --

07:17.834 --> 07:19.867
ERIC, YOU'RE GONNA
KNOCK OVER THE CANDLES!

07:19.867 --> 07:21.400
ERIC!

07:21.400 --> 07:23.767
♪ FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW ♪

07:23.767 --> 07:25.500
♪ FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW ♪

07:25.500 --> 07:28.033
OH, MY GOD!
LOOK, IT'S HAPPENING!

07:28.033 --> 07:30.700
ERIC!
LOOK WHAT YOU DID! ERIC!

07:30.700 --> 07:32.734
♪ THE CURTAINS
ARE ON FIRE ♪

07:32.734 --> 07:34.967
♪ THE CURTAINS
ARE ON FIRE ♪

07:34.967 --> 07:36.500
AAAH! AAAH!

07:36.500 --> 07:38.500
♪ THEY'RE CHOPPING UP
THE DORM ROOM ♪

07:38.500 --> 07:40.400
♪ THEY'RE CHOPPING UP
THE DORM ROOM ♪

07:40.400 --> 07:43.000
♪ MY BROTHER IS A MORON! ♪

07:43.000 --> 07:44.867
♪ WHICH NOBODY CAN DENY ♪

07:44.867 --> 07:47.233
HEY! [ CHUCKLES ]

07:47.233 --> 07:48.033
AAAAH!

07:50.400 --> 07:52.200
AND THAT'S WHY SHAWN'S
MY BEST MAN,

07:52.200 --> 07:53.567
AND SHAWN'S MY BEST MAN,

07:53.567 --> 07:58.400
AND I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ANYTHING FROM ANYBODY!

07:58.400 --> 07:59.767
<i>YOU </i>TALK NOW.

07:59.767 --> 08:01.867
I'VE GOT, LIKE,
A RIP HERE IN MY PANCREAS.

08:01.867 --> 08:04.367
HE'S ALWAYS SO TENSE.
I DON'T KNOW WHY THAT IS.

08:04.367 --> 08:07.200
NO, BUT YOU KNOW WHERE
THE <i>SHOE </i>DEPARTMENT IS.

08:07.200 --> 08:09.600
CAN WE PLEASE TALK
ABOUT SOMETHING POSITIVE?

08:09.600 --> 08:11.233
WHAT WAS POSITIVE?

08:11.233 --> 08:13.200
HOW ABOUT THOSE TALKS
YOU HAD WITH YOUR FATHER --

08:13.200 --> 08:15.500
HOW PROUD HE IS
OF HIS LITTLE MAN?

08:15.500 --> 08:18.567
YEAH, DAD AND I
HAD SOME TALKS, ALL RIGHT.

08:18.567 --> 08:21.834
YOU CHOSE SHAWN AS YOUR BEST MAN
OVER YOUR OWN FLESH AND BLOOD?

08:21.834 --> 08:23.400
YOU'RE DEAD TO ME.

08:23.400 --> 08:24.700
WHAT DID I JUST HEAR?

08:24.700 --> 08:25.900
"YOU'RE DEAD TO ME."

08:25.900 --> 08:29.000
YOUR HUSBAND JUST SAID THAT
TO YOUR OWN SON.

08:29.000 --> 08:30.300
ALAN!

08:30.300 --> 08:32.600
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW <i>SCARRING </i>THAT IS?

08:32.600 --> 08:35.867
ALAN!
HE CHOSE SHAWN
AS HIS BEST MAN.

08:35.867 --> 08:37.400
YOU SCUM.

08:37.400 --> 08:39.567
SIT DOWN, CORY.

08:39.567 --> 08:41.500
YEAH, SIT DOWN, SCUM.

08:41.500 --> 08:44.934
LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED TO THIS FAMILY.

08:44.934 --> 08:46.734
YOUR MOTHER AND I MET,

08:46.734 --> 08:49.800
AND WE FELL IN LOVE,
AND WE GOT MARRIED,

08:49.800 --> 08:52.300
AND FROM THAT LOVE,
WE HAD A SON.

08:54.500 --> 08:59.233
AND WE WERE A FAMILY --
YOUR MOTHER, ME, AND ERIC.

08:59.233 --> 09:01.133
AND YET,
THERE WAS A VOID.

09:01.133 --> 09:03.867
AND ERIC,
MORE THAN ANYTHING ELSE,

09:03.867 --> 09:06.834
WANTED A BABY BROTHER --
MORE THAN <i>ANYTHING </i>ELSE.

09:06.834 --> 09:08.367
I LOVE YOU, CORY.

09:08.367 --> 09:12.600
AND WE HAD <i>YOU, </i>CORY,
AND ERIC HAD A BROTHER.

09:12.600 --> 09:16.767
AND THE TWO OF YOU COULD GO
THROUGH THE WORLD TOGETHER...

09:16.767 --> 09:18.800
LOOKING OUT FOR EACH OTHER,
TAKING CARE OF EACH OTHER...

09:18.800 --> 09:20.734
PUTTING EACH OTHER FIRST.

09:20.734 --> 09:22.000
THAT'S ALL I WANTED.

09:23.600 --> 09:25.467
NOW, WE HAVEN'T ASKED
MUCH FROM YOU.

09:25.467 --> 09:27.400
BUT THEY'RE
GONNA ASK SOMETHING NOW.

09:27.400 --> 09:28.734
IT'S YOUR DECISION,

09:28.734 --> 09:31.500
BUT IF IT MEANS
<i>ANYTHING </i>TO YOU,

09:31.500 --> 09:35.400
WE WOULD LIKE YOUR BROTHER
TO BE YOUR BEST MAN.

09:35.400 --> 09:39.500
YEAH. FINE, GOOD --
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

09:39.500 --> 09:41.934
YEAH!
ERIC MATTHEWS, BEST MAN!

09:41.934 --> 09:43.567
I ACCEPT, MY BROTHER!

09:43.567 --> 09:46.367
I KIND OF KNEW
THAT WAS GONNA HAPPEN --

09:46.367 --> 09:48.133
HAD A LITTLE FEELING --

09:48.133 --> 09:50.500
SO I THINK THIS CALLS
FOR A CELEBRATION.

09:50.500 --> 09:51.767
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:51.767 --> 09:52.967
WATCH THIS.

09:55.000 --> 09:59.400
THIS IS THE ETERNAL FLAME
OF THE LOVE OF THE MATTHEWS --

09:59.400 --> 10:00.700
HOT!

10:00.700 --> 10:02.700
[ SIZZLING ]

10:11.600 --> 10:13.100
HE'S OUT! SHAWN'S IN!

10:13.100 --> 10:16.133
SOMEBODY SAVE THE BABY!
SOMEBODY SAVE THE BABY!

10:19.500 --> 10:22.100
SPARKLERS ARE FUN!

10:25.400 --> 10:27.400
Cory: SO, ANYWAY,

10:27.400 --> 10:30.300
I HAVE MY BEST MAN,
AND I'M VERY HAPPY.

10:30.300 --> 10:31.600
I'M NOT.

10:31.600 --> 10:34.000
YES, BUT I <i>AM... </i>

10:34.000 --> 10:37.200
AND I AM DON FRANCISCO.

10:37.200 --> 10:40.600
I MEAN, I KNOW IT WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE AN HONOR AND EVERYTHING,

10:40.600 --> 10:43.867
BUT...COME ON.

10:43.867 --> 10:47.100
COME ON,
WHAT'S TAKING YOU SO LONG?!

10:47.100 --> 10:48.734
COME ON, COME ON,

10:48.734 --> 10:51.367
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON!

11:00.667 --> 11:02.667
OH, WILL YOU LOOK AT THAT?!

11:02.667 --> 11:05.934
MY WEDDING DRESS
FITS YOU <i>PERFECTLY! </i>

11:10.367 --> 11:12.500
I MEAN, I DON'T
WANT TO OFFEND ANYONE,

11:12.500 --> 11:15.834
AND MY FAMILY'S FEELINGS ARE
THE MOST IMPORTANT THING TO ME,

11:15.834 --> 11:18.133
BUT IF SHE THOUGHT
I WAS GETTING MARRIED

11:18.133 --> 11:19.467
IN THAT
FREAKING MONSTROSITY,

11:19.467 --> 11:22.000
SHE MUST HAVE BEEN
HITTING THE SAUCE.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.734
VERY NICE.

11:23.734 --> 11:26.400
I WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT THIS GOWN

11:26.400 --> 11:29.900
HAS BEEN IN MY FAMILY
SINCE THE CIVIL WAR.

11:29.900 --> 11:33.133
MUSTY LITTLE DEVIL,
AIN'T IT?

11:33.133 --> 11:35.367
EVERY WOMAN
IN MY FAMILY HISTORY

11:35.367 --> 11:36.900
THAT HAS WORN THIS DRESS

11:36.900 --> 11:39.100
HAS HAD A LONG
AND HEALTHY LIFE.

11:39.100 --> 11:43.100
IN FACT, EXCEPT
FOR THE ENGAGEMENT RING --

11:43.100 --> 11:45.867
WHICH I ALREADY
GAVE TO YOU --

11:45.867 --> 11:50.400
THERE IS NO MORE IMPORTANT
POSSESSION THAT I OWN.

11:50.400 --> 11:55.100
SO PLEASE DO ME THE HONOR
OF BEING MARRIED IN IT.

11:55.100 --> 11:57.934
OHH...

11:57.934 --> 12:00.100
POOH.

12:00.100 --> 12:04.500
[ Imitating Topanga ]
THAT IS THE MOST <i>BEAUTIFUL </i>DRESS

12:04.500 --> 12:08.200
I'VE EVER SEEN!

12:08.200 --> 12:10.967
OH, YOU'RE HAPPY
FOR YOUR NEW SISTER.

12:10.967 --> 12:15.133
YEP. I THINK SHE <i>DESERVES  </i>
THAT DRESS.

12:15.133 --> 12:16.867
BITE ME.

12:19.300 --> 12:20.467
I DON'T KNOW.

12:20.467 --> 12:24.300
I JUST LASHED OUT.

12:24.300 --> 12:26.033
IT WAS AS IF I WAS POSSESSED

12:26.033 --> 12:27.500
BY THE GHOST
OF YOUR NANA BOO BOO.

12:27.500 --> 12:32.834
[ Crying ] NANA BOO BOO!
I MISS YOU!

12:32.834 --> 12:34.000
IS NANA BOO BOO DEAD?

12:34.000 --> 12:35.033
NO.

12:35.033 --> 12:36.133
NO. GOOD, GOOD.

12:36.133 --> 12:38.934
AND SO IT WAS
AT THIS CRUCIAL POINT

12:38.934 --> 12:41.500
OF THE CHAOS
WHICH IS OUR WEDDING

12:41.500 --> 12:44.567
THAT WE FINALLY DECIDED
TO REGAIN CONTROL

12:44.567 --> 12:46.834
AND CALL IN...
A PROFESSIONAL.

12:46.834 --> 12:50.200
WHEN JUDY HABERFELD
PLANS YOUR WEDDING,

12:50.200 --> 12:52.934
JUDY HABERFELD
IS THERE FOR YOU.

12:52.934 --> 12:57.133
FROM GUESTLIST TO GUEST <i>LAST </i>
--[ CHUCKLES ]

12:57.133 --> 13:00.133
FROM FIRST DANCE
TO GRAND FINALE,

13:00.133 --> 13:04.400
THERE IS NO DETAIL
TOO SMALL FOR JUDY HABERFELD.

13:04.400 --> 13:06.900
WE'VE HEARD WONDERFUL THINGS
ABOUT YOU, MISS HABERFELD.

13:06.900 --> 13:12.300
OHH. PLEASE, CALL ME
<i>JUDY </i>HABERFELD.

13:12.300 --> 13:14.133
I'M SO SORRY WE'RE LATE.

13:14.133 --> 13:16.567
HOPE WE DIDN'T MISS
THE PLANNING,

13:16.567 --> 13:18.367
BUT YOU COULDN'T BE
TOO FAR IN

13:18.367 --> 13:20.700
BECAUSE MY WALLET
DOESN'T FEEL ANY LIGHTER.

13:20.700 --> 13:22.400
[ As Ed McMahon ]
HEY-OHH!

13:22.400 --> 13:24.133
OH, MY.

13:24.133 --> 13:26.800
ALL RIGHT,
WELL, THAT'S ENOUGH.

13:26.800 --> 13:29.400
UM, ABOUT THE GUESTLIST --

13:29.400 --> 13:32.700
I UNDERSTAND
THIS HALL SEATS 80,

13:32.700 --> 13:36.000
BUT I CAN'T <i>POSSIBLY </i>
FIT MORE THAN 65

13:36.000 --> 13:39.400
WITH THE THEME
OUR BRIDE HAS IN MIND.

13:39.400 --> 13:41.400
UM, BUT WE INVITED 270.

13:41.400 --> 13:44.233
[ LAUGHS ]

13:44.233 --> 13:48.800
ALL RIGHT, NOW, I UNDERSTAND
THAT THE FATHER OF THE GROOM

13:48.800 --> 13:52.400
HAS AGREED TO PAY FOR
THE BEVERAGES AND THE MUSIC.

13:52.400 --> 13:55.834
AND WITH THE BUDGET
YOU HAVE ALLOWED ME,

13:55.834 --> 13:59.467
I HAVE ASSEMBLED YOUR MUSICAL...
CHOICES...OVER THERE.

14:10.500 --> 14:12.700
CRUISE BUSINESS
A LITTLE SLOW, BOYS?

14:12.700 --> 14:15.700
YEAH.
YEAH.
YEAH.
YEAH.

14:15.700 --> 14:17.667
DON'T WORRY, COR,
I GOT YOU COVERED.

14:17.667 --> 14:19.000
HEY-OHH!

14:19.000 --> 14:20.600
COME ON IN!

14:20.600 --> 14:23.100
[ TRUMPET PLAYS ]

14:31.200 --> 14:33.800
OH, YEAH!

14:36.000 --> 14:38.667
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW HARD IT IS...

14:38.667 --> 14:40.500
TO KEEP
A SMILE ON YOUR FACE...

14:40.500 --> 14:42.734
UNDER THESE CIRCUMSTANCES?

14:42.734 --> 14:46.100
ISN'T IT WONDERFUL, CORY?

14:46.100 --> 14:48.934
GEORGE AND HIS JAZZ GROUP
HAVE AGREED

14:48.934 --> 14:52.133
TO BE THE BAND
AT YOUR RECEPTION...FOR FREE!

14:52.133 --> 14:55.667
CONSIDER IT MY PRESENT
TO THE BRIDE AND GROOM.

14:55.667 --> 15:01.100
A BLENDER
WOULD HAVE BEEN JUST LOVELY.

15:01.100 --> 15:04.200
NOW, IF I CAN JUST FIGURE OUT
HOW TO WATER DOWN THE DRINKS,

15:04.200 --> 15:07.300
I COULD GET OUT OF THIS
WHOLE THING FOR ABOUT 70 BUCKS!

15:07.300 --> 15:10.700
[ Singsong voice ]
GEORGIE?

15:13.233 --> 15:16.867
GEORGIE FEENY,
IS THAT YOU?

15:16.867 --> 15:19.200
Oh, please, no.

15:19.200 --> 15:21.200
GEORGIE, IT'S ME --

15:21.200 --> 15:24.967
JUDY...HABERFELD --
JUDY HABERFELD!

15:24.967 --> 15:26.600
JUDY!

15:26.600 --> 15:29.100
HABERFELD!

15:29.100 --> 15:31.767
YOU KNOW,
I WAS GONNA CALL...

15:31.767 --> 15:35.100
I WAS, B-B-BUT I MOVED...
OUT OF STATE --

15:35.100 --> 15:37.500
UH, MISSION
FOR THE GOVERNMENT --

15:37.500 --> 15:39.500
ESPIONAGE --

15:39.500 --> 15:42.233
ALL VERY HUSH-HUSH.

15:42.233 --> 15:45.233
[ IMITATES RINGING ]

15:45.233 --> 15:47.400
WHAT DO YOU GOT FOR ME,
CHIEF?

15:49.567 --> 15:52.100
NORTH KOREA? DAMN.

15:52.100 --> 15:53.667
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

16:01.600 --> 16:04.767
DO YOU KNOW,
THEY <i>ALL </i>DO THAT...

16:04.767 --> 16:08.967
EVERY <i>STINKING </i>ONE OF THEM.

16:08.967 --> 16:11.834
BUT I PLOW ON.

16:11.834 --> 16:14.300
HEY, FEENY JUST JUMPED
OVER A WALL

16:14.300 --> 16:16.233
AND LANDED IN THE POOL.

16:16.233 --> 16:20.200
TELL ME, WHO IS THIS PERSON?
I'M JUDY HABERFELD.

16:20.200 --> 16:22.834
YEAH, THAT'S THE NAME
HE WAS SCREAMING.

16:22.834 --> 16:24.367
WHAT'S UP, GUYS?

16:24.367 --> 16:26.233
WE'RE OVERBOOKED
BY, LIKE, 1,000,

16:26.233 --> 16:29.400
DAD'S TRYING TO SAVE MONEY
BY USING <i>FEENY </i>AS THE BAND,

16:29.400 --> 16:32.100
AND TOPANGA'S LEFT EYE
IS BEGINNING TO TWITCH.

16:32.100 --> 16:33.934
IT IS NOT!

16:36.000 --> 16:38.800
WELL, TOPANGA,
HAVE I GOT A SURPRISE FOR YOU.

16:38.800 --> 16:40.467
PLEASE, NO.

16:40.467 --> 16:43.834
LADIES, FRONT AND CENTER!

16:43.834 --> 16:46.367
LET'S GO, COME ON!

16:46.367 --> 16:48.867
HUH? HA HA HA!

16:48.867 --> 16:50.100
OKAY, WHO WANTS TO GO FIRST?

16:53.400 --> 16:57.000
I TOTALLY LOVE
MY BRIDESMAID'S DRESS.

16:57.000 --> 17:00.600
I TOTALLY LOVE
MY BRIDESMAID'S DRESS.

17:01.900 --> 17:05.000
I FEEL LIKE
A DELICATE GEORGIA PEACH

17:05.000 --> 17:08.400
IN THIS DRESS,
AND I'M THRILLED TO WEAR IT.

17:08.400 --> 17:10.100
THANK YOU.

17:12.467 --> 17:14.567
I WAS VERY SELFISH
AND INCONSIDERATE YESTERDAY.

17:14.567 --> 17:17.033
THIS IS <i>YOUR </i>WEDDING AND I'M
GOING TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH.

17:19.467 --> 17:21.200
YOUR FRIENDS
ARE STINKING LIARS!

17:21.200 --> 17:22.600
SHAWN PAID THEM
50 BUCKS EACH,

17:22.600 --> 17:25.467
AND <i>I </i>WOULDN'T USE THIS
DRESS TO WIPE MY --

17:25.467 --> 17:26.967
[ LAUGHING ]

17:26.967 --> 17:30.367
[ Muffled ]
I HATE THIS DRESS!

17:38.233 --> 17:39.900
HELLO, EVERYONE.

17:41.500 --> 17:43.834
OKAY, DON'T DO THIS.
LOOK AT ME. I'M <i>BEGGING </i>YOU.

17:43.834 --> 17:46.233
QUIET, HALF-BREED!

17:46.233 --> 17:48.500
THERE ARE SOME PEOPLE
IN THIS ROOM

17:48.500 --> 17:52.133
WHO SHALL REMAIN NAMELESS --
CORY AND MOMMY AND DADDY! --

17:52.133 --> 17:54.567
THAT DON'T THINK
I'M BEST-MAN MATERIAL.

17:54.567 --> 17:57.100
WELL, I'M SORRY
I HAVE TO DO THIS, CORY.

17:58.667 --> 18:00.967
Look, rethink this, all right?
It's a <i>bad </i>move.

18:00.967 --> 18:03.834
[ SHUSHES ]

18:03.834 --> 18:06.133
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, TOPANGA?

18:06.133 --> 18:08.767
IF I CAN'T BE
THE BEST MAN...

18:08.767 --> 18:10.900
THEN I'M GONNA BE THE GROOM.

18:16.000 --> 18:18.400
TOPANGA, I LOVE YOU.

18:18.400 --> 18:20.567
I'VE <i>ALWAYS </i>LOVED YOU,

18:20.567 --> 18:23.767
EVER SINCE I SAW YOU
THROUGH THAT PEEPHOLE

18:23.767 --> 18:26.400
IN THE BATHROOM.

18:28.600 --> 18:33.834
AND I KNOW HOW YOU'VE
SECRETLY LONGED FOR ME AS WELL.

18:33.834 --> 18:37.967
SO, TOPANGA, LET'S JUST
<i>DROP </i>THIS CHARADE.

18:40.300 --> 18:45.300
TOPANGA, MARRY ME,
AND LET'S MAKE NICK-NICK.

18:45.300 --> 18:47.033
GET HIM.
AAAHHHHHHH!

18:47.033 --> 18:50.300
Topanga: I'M AFRAID THAT
ALL OF OUR HORRIBLE EXPERIENCES

18:50.300 --> 18:51.700
HAVE BROUGHT US HERE.

18:51.700 --> 18:54.400
WE KNEW THAT PLANNING A WEDDING
WAS GONNA BE TOUGH,

18:54.400 --> 18:55.867
BUT I DON'T THINK ANY OF US

18:55.867 --> 18:58.033
ARE GONNA SURVIVE
THIS ENGAGEMENT.

18:58.033 --> 19:00.400
THERE'S NO WAY
WE'LL MAKE IT UNTIL JUNE.

19:00.400 --> 19:01.800
THERE'S JUST NO WAY.

19:01.800 --> 19:04.300
I'LL DO SOMETHING <i>VERY  </i>
BAD TO ERIC.

19:04.300 --> 19:07.000
I WILL.

19:07.000 --> 19:08.567
HONEY...

19:08.567 --> 19:12.400
I KNOW! I'M TWITCHING!
BACK OFF!

19:12.400 --> 19:15.100
PLEASE, WE'RE ASKING YOU
TO UNDERSTAND.

19:15.100 --> 19:17.500
THIS WEDDING IS THE MOST
IMPORTANT DAY OF OUR LIVES.

19:17.500 --> 19:21.100
BUT YOU PEOPLE HAVE TURNED
THIS SACRED, BEAUTIFUL EVENT

19:21.100 --> 19:23.033
INTO A FREAK SHOW.

19:23.033 --> 19:25.400
WE ALL MEAN WELL,
WE JUST DON'T THINK

19:25.400 --> 19:28.734
WE'RE GONNA BE ABLE TO SURVIVE
AN 8-MONTH ENGAGEMENT.

19:28.734 --> 19:30.500
WE WANT TO GET MARRIED
NEXT WEEK.

19:30.500 --> 19:32.834
NO WEDDING HALL,
NO FANCY PLANNER,

19:32.834 --> 19:34.834
JUST OUR FRIENDS
AND FAMILY.

19:34.834 --> 19:37.033
ALL THE PEOPLE
WHO CARE ABOUT US

19:37.033 --> 19:40.700
RIGHT HERE, NEXT FRIDAY NIGHT,
8:00 -- 7:00 CENTRAL.

19:40.700 --> 19:43.400
Mr. Feeny:
UH, ONE QUESTION.

19:43.400 --> 19:45.500
MR. FEENY?

19:45.500 --> 19:47.934
YOU'RE GONNA GO THROUGH
WITH IT THIS TIME,

19:47.934 --> 19:49.233
AREN'T YOU?

20:07.500 --> 20:09.000
WE'RE FINALLY DOING IT,

20:09.000 --> 20:10.300
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED.

20:10.300 --> 20:12.734
AND WE WANT YOU TO BE THERE,
THIS TIME, NEXT FRIDAY NIGHT.

20:12.734 --> 20:14.500
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK SO CUTE
IN A TUXEDO.

20:14.500 --> 20:16.600
YEAH, IT'S POWDER BLUE.
NO, IT'S NOT.

20:16.600 --> 20:19.000
ALL OUR FRIENDS ARE GONNA
BE THERE, INCLUDING YOU.

20:19.000 --> 20:20.934
IT WOULDN'T BE THE SAME
WITHOUT YOU.

20:20.934 --> 20:22.967
SO PLEASE R.S.V.P.
TO OUR WEB SITE...

20:22.967 --> 20:24.300
coryandtopanga.com.

20:24.300 --> 20:26.767
SEE, CORYANDTOPANGA --
ONE WORD --

20:26.767 --> 20:28.133
IS SORT OF LIKE
A SYMBOL OF OUR UNITY.

20:28.133 --> 20:29.834
NO, IT'S A COMPUTER THING.

20:29.834 --> 20:31.800
UNITY!
coryandtopanga.com.

20:31.800 --> 20:33.300
SEE YOU AT OUR WEDDING.
